{
  "stem": "8784.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 88,
      "text": "You go under that straw, and he takes you right through the Polish border.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 89,
      "text": "And the Polish guards will not dare asking a Russian whether he has any passengers or not.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 90,
      "text": "And that's how I cross the border from Poland into Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 91,
      "text": "Then from Czechoslovakia, I had to continue.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 92,
      "text": "I had to cross all of Czechoslovakia-- the full length, and get to the part of West Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 93,
      "text": "And at that time I also crossed the border.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 94,
      "text": "By simply-- I mean, fear was just not in me anymore.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 95,
      "text": "I felt that maybe the world owes me something at that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 96,
      "text": "And I actually got on a mountain, where I climbed the mountain, and over the mountain, I came into West Germany, where I settled in Bamberg.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 97,
      "text": "And from then on, together with Adam Mandel and then some other friends by the name of Szymek Szajn and-- and Karl Diamond, we formed a kind of a family unit, where we lived in Bamberg, Germany.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 98,
      "text": "In Bamberg, we arrived still in October of 1945.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 99,
      "text": "And when we arrived there, the Germans were not hostile at all towards us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 100,
      "text": "We wanted to be there because the Americans were there, and we knew that they would provide us with a kind of a security blanket.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 101,
      "text": "But the Germans were extremely accommodating at that time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 102,
      "text": "And they-- and most of them did not know anything about what their compatriots or what their family members did during the war-- that in fact, many people were killed.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 103,
      "text": "They were extremely anxious to-- to do anything they can for us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 104,
      "text": "A German landlady gave up her two rooms for us to settle in her house.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 105,
      "text": "And we were the guests of the German landlady in Bamberg.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
